  "title": "State Continuing Education Requirements",
  "body": "<html><body><div id=\"block-ti-west-content\">\n<article>\n<div>\n<div>\n\n<div class=\"hero__container hero__container--text-dark hero__container--no-overlay\" data-hero-container=\"\">\n<div class=\"container container--max-width\">\n<div class=\"hero__text-inset\">\n<div class=\"container__grid container__grid--3col--big-center\">\n<div class=\"hero__text-container hero__text-container--center\">\n<h1 class=\"u-margin-hug u-font-family-secondary hero__title\">State Continuing Education Requirements</h1>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n\n</div>\n<div><div data-react-component-id=\"state-ce-requirements\"></div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"container container--max-width paragraph paragraph--type--text paragraph--view-mode--default\">\n<div><p><em>State continuing education requirements may change. While we strive to keep information current, we recommend confirming your CE requirements directly with your state department of insurance before enrolling. You can find contact information for your state department through the</em><a href=\"https://content.naic.org/state-insurance-departments\" target=\"_blank\"><em> National Association of Insurance Commissioners (NAIC)</em></a><em> directory.</em></p></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</article>\n</div></body></html>",
